  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book *Dies irae*, published by Leuven University Press in 2021, currently lacks documented citations and online discourse, indicating a limited academic reach at this time. However, the presence of commercial linkages through platforms like Amazon and Goodreads suggests potential interest among readers.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Since its publication in 2021 by Leuven University Press, *Dies irae* has not recorded any formal academic citations or public discussions through high-fidelity platforms. This suggests that while the work exists within the academic space, its visibility and impact may be limited at present. The absence of community discourse platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit further underscores the current low engagement with the scholarly and public audience.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The metadata indicates strong commercial linkages, evidenced by its availability on major online platforms like Amazon and Goodreads. This could imply that *Dies irae* may attract interest among general readers, potentially signaling a niche market outside of mainstream academic recognition. Such pathways are critical for works that aim to enter public consciousness and stimulate conversation beyond academic circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the absence of high engagement metrics is notable, it does not diminish the book\u2019s potential for future relevance. As it stands, the landscape may evolve over time, particularly if the subject matter resonates with changing societal interests or scholarly trends. The lack of any events or online mentions at this stage indicates an opportunity for the authors and publisher to engage more actively with potential audiences.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, *Dies irae* is currently navigating a phase of low visibility but presents a commercial presence that may foster future discussions. If engagement metrics improve, it could signal a growth trajectory, allowing the book to fulfill its academic and societal relevance over time.</p>",
